   "source": [
    "# 28. What are the different types of bias in Machine Learning?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "fec4b67e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In ML interviews, “bias” can mean different things depending on context. A strong answer shows you know all major categories:\n",
    "\n",
    "✅ 1. Statistical Bias (Model Bias)\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Error due to oversimplified assumptions\n",
    "\n",
    "Example: Using a linear model for non-linear data\n",
    "Leads to underfitting\n",
    "\n",
    "✔️ Part of Bias–Variance tradeoff\n",
    "\n",
    "✅ 2. Data Bias (Most important in real-world)\n",
    "\n",
    "Bias introduced from the dataset itself\n",
    "\n",
    "🔹 Types of Data Bias\n",
    "🔸 Sampling Bias\n",
    "Data not representative of population\n",
    "Example: Survey only urban users\n",
    "🔸 Class Imbalance Bias\n",
    "One class dominates (e.g., 95% vs 5%)\n",
    "🔸 Measurement Bias\n",
    "Errors in data collection\n",
    "Example: faulty sensors\n",
    "🔸 Label Bias\n",
    "Incorrect or subjective labels\n",
    "Example: human annotation errors\n",
    "🔸 Survivorship Bias\n",
    "Only successful cases are considered\n",
    "Ignoring failures\n",
    "✅ 3. Algorithmic Bias\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Bias introduced by the learning algorithm\n",
    "\n",
    "Model favors certain patterns/groups\n",
    "Can lead to unfair predictions\n",
    "\n",
    "Example:\n",
    "\n",
    "Biased hiring model favoring certain profiles\n",
    "✅ 4. Cognitive Bias (Human Bias)\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Bias from human decisions in ML pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "Feature selection bias\n",
    "Confirmation bias\n",
    "✅ 5. Historical Bias\n",
    "Bias already present in real-world data\n",
    "Model learns and replicates it\n",
    "✅ 6. Evaluation Bias\n",
    "Wrong metrics or validation approach\n",
    "Example: using accuracy on imbalanced data\n",
    "🎯 Interview-Ready Answer (Short)**\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 “Bias in machine learning can refer to statistical bias, which leads to underfitting, and data-related biases such as sampling, label, and measurement bias. Additionally, algorithmic bias and human biases can also affect model fairness and performance.”\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 Pro Tip\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Always mention:\n",
    "\n",
    "Bias–Variance tradeoff (technical)\n",
    "Data bias (real-world impact)\n",
    "🚀 Bonus (Stand-out Answer)\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 “Bias is not just a modeling issue—it can originate from data, algorithms, or human decisions, and addressing it is critical for both model performance and fairness.”"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1adec12d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Give me tricky interview questions on bias"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "2930dd4f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Here are tricky, high-level interview questions on bias (the kind asked in companies like Amazon, Accenture, KPMG).\n",
    "I’ve included what the interviewer is testing + how you should think 👇\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 1. Accuracy is high, but model is unfair. Why?\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 What’s going on?\n",
    "\n",
    "Expected thinking:\n",
    "\n",
    "Dataset may be imbalanced across groups\n",
    "Model biased toward majority group\n",
    "Accuracy hides unfairness\n",
    "\n",
    "✔️ Mention:\n",
    "\n",
    "Fairness metrics (demographic parity, equal opportunity)\n",
    "🔥 2. You removed sensitive features (gender, race), but bias still exists. Why?\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Very common trap\n",
    "\n",
    "Answer:\n",
    "\n",
    "Proxy variables (e.g., zip code → race)\n",
    "Correlated features still carry bias\n",
    "\n",
    "✔️ Key term:\n",
    "👉 “Indirect discrimination via proxy features”\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 3. Is bias always bad in ML?\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Twist question\n",
    "\n",
    "Answer:\n",
    "\n",
    "❌ Not always\n",
    "✔️ Inductive bias is necessary for learning\n",
    "\n",
    "✔️ Example:\n",
    "\n",
    "Linear regression assumes linearity\n",
    "🔥 4. How do you detect bias without ground truth fairness labels?\n",
    "\n",
    "Expected answer:\n",
    "\n",
    "Compare model performance across groups\n",
    "Analyze:\n",
    "Precision / Recall per group\n",
    "Distribution analysis\n",
    "🔥 5. If you balance the dataset, is bias completely solved?\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Trap\n",
    "\n",
    "Answer:\n",
    "\n",
    "❌ No\n",
    "Bias can still exist due to:\n",
    "Feature representation\n",
    "Model design\n",
    "Historical bias\n",
    "🔥 6. Can removing outliers introduce bias?\n",
    "\n",
    "Answer:\n",
    "\n",
    "✔️ Yes\n",
    "If outliers belong to minority group → removing them = bias\n",
    "🔥 7. You trained on historical data. What bias can occur?\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Answer:\n",
    "\n",
    "Historical bias\n",
    "\n",
    "✔️ Model learns past discrimination patterns\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 8. When can data cleaning introduce bias?\n",
    "\n",
    "Answer:\n",
    "\n",
    "Removing missing values unevenly across groups\n",
    "Filtering data incorrectly\n",
    "🔥 9. Bias vs Variance—can reducing one increase the other?\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Core concept:\n",
    "\n",
    "✔️ Yes → tradeoff\n",
    "\n",
    "Reducing bias → may increase variance\n",
    "Reducing variance → may increase bias\n",
    "🔥 10. Model performs well offline but fails in production. Bias issue?\n",
    "\n",
    "Answer:\n",
    "\n",
    "Train-serving skew\n",
    "Sampling bias\n",
    "Distribution shift\n",
    "🔥 11. What is survivorship bias in ML?\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Answer:\n",
    "\n",
    "Only successful cases considered\n",
    "Failures ignored\n",
    "\n",
    "Example:\n",
    "\n",
    "Studying only successful startups\n",
    "🔥 12. How would you fix bias in a hiring model?\n",
    "\n",
    "Expected structured answer:\n",
    "\n",
    "Audit dataset\n",
    "Remove proxy features\n",
    "Use fairness constraints\n",
    "Evaluate fairness metrics\n",
    "Monitor continuously\n",
    "🔥 13. Can deep learning models reduce bias automatically?\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Answer:\n",
    "\n",
    "❌ No\n",
    "They can amplify bias if data is biased\n",
    "🔥 14. What is measurement bias?\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Answer:\n",
    "\n",
    "Errors in data collection\n",
    "Example: faulty sensors, subjective labeling\n",
    "🔥 15. How do you handle bias in recommendation systems?\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Answer:\n",
    "\n",
    "Avoid popularity bias\n",
    "Ensure diversity\n",
    "Use re-ranking strategies\n",
    "🎯 Perfect Closing Answer (Use in Interview)\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 “Bias in ML can originate from data, features, or algorithms. Detecting it requires group-wise evaluation, and mitigating it involves careful data preprocessing, feature selection, and fairness-aware modeling.”\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 Pro Tip (High Impact Line)\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 “Removing sensitive attributes doesn’t guarantee fairness due to proxy variables.”"
   ]
  },
